The paper deals with approximation algorithms for clustering problems on planar graphs, which are fundamental topics in computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on the $k$-Median problem, which is a classic clustering problem. The problem is defined on a graph, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) categories. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which are related to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. Finally, the paper uses mathematical tools such as coreset constructions, which are related to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) category.
